ng, the selection of presidential electors, and the reapportionment of the House of Representatives. Only in 1850 did the conflict based on state size merge with, and become subsumed by, the growing controversy between North and South.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFederal governmentzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRepresentative government and representationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aState governmentszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aGeography-Physical & Cultural. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aU.S. History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171136740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501711367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501711367/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles